cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a foraging algorithm for robot swarms, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a genetic algorithm to optimize the foraging strategy suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.MA). The coordination of the swarm without central control implies a focus on distributed systems (cs.SY). The use of ant-inspired algorithms suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the optimization of the algorithm through a genetic algorithm suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
